  <problem>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Service Identification practice discovers, describes, and classifies a collection of candidate services that, when&#xD;
    specified and realized, will satisfy&amp;nbsp;targeted requirements of the business.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This practice:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Reduces the time-to-value for SOA projects.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Performing the practice's techniques increases the chance&#xD;
        that&amp;nbsp;one pass through Service Identification will be enough to identify&amp;nbsp;all the&amp;nbsp;services that are&#xD;
        necessary to realize the requirements that are being considered.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Improves the quality of business results by&amp;nbsp;producing a set of candidate services that are provably&#xD;
        business-aligned.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Improves audit results by establishing traceability from business-relevant precursors to candidate services.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></problem>
  <application>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To understand this practice, begin by reading the key concepts:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp-ibm/guidances/concepts/service_2D3C4FFE.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_OMw8cEozEd6D_7XK49c0nw&quot;>Service&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/concepts/candidate_service_277B23D6.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_R5GZYEo1Ed6D_7XK49c0nw&quot;>Candidate Service&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/concepts/service_model_FC39652E.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_T-AiUEozEd6D_7XK49c0nw&quot;>Service Model&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    You will also need to understand the Object Management Group's SoaML notation for describing service-oriented&#xD;
    systems.&amp;nbsp; Read &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/concepts/soaml_4074BA7B.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_XsWMIFIREd6lNtylJFsPIg&quot;>SoaML&lt;/a> and the SoaML-related concepts and guidances that article references.&amp;nbsp; It&#xD;
    will be useful to download the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/whitepapers/soaml_specification_8B377FF3.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_FYb84EovEd6D_7XK49c0nw&quot;>SoaML Specification&lt;/a> for detailed reference.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Once you understand the above concepts and have a basic familiarity with SoaML, then review the tasks and guidances of&#xD;
    the practice.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    As you work through the tasks and guidance, examine the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/examples/soaml_design_model_sample_83612289.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_AfQisHNIEd6va-EJWoOsvg&quot;>SoaML sample model&lt;/a> to see how the elements created during the tasks might be&#xD;
    integrated into a service model.&amp;nbsp; Refer to the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_soa-ibm/guidances/guidelines/service_model_structure_6E84F997.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_qHU5sFIREd6lNtylJFsPIg&quot;>Service Model Structure&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;guidelines to stay on track with respect to organizing&#xD;
    your service model.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For step-by-step instructions on how to adopt this practice, see &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soma.service_identification.base-ibm/guidances/roadmaps/how_to_adopt_service_identification_C1765C40.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_L2c_YFIVEd6lNtylJFsPIg&quot;>How to Adopt the Service Identification Practice&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></application>
